    "Ans:-\n",
    "The sentence \"import areallyourpetsnamederic\" does not have any specific built-in meaning in Python. It appears to be an arbitrary statement that is unlikely to be a valid Python import statement.\n",
    "In Python, the import statement is used to import modules or packages that contain reusable code. The module or package specified after the import keyword should be a valid Python module or package name. In this case, \"areallyourpetsnamederic\" does not appear to be a standard Python module or package name, so this import statement would result in an error.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
